Guild Message</span><hr size=1> Beloved Arrows,<br>
<br>
Most of you do not know me, some do. Some may have even heard my name echoed in the halls and taverns with drunken bards singing tales of a fair ranger lady of the glade and her dreams of forming an alliance with friends and cohorts who had common goals and values.<br>
Well that was indeed me, and I am one of the founding members of our brave guild. We went through alot in the short period of time whence I laid my steel towards the common good of our people. But alas, like most other things, I was drawn away on many quests that were personal in nature. Instead of nurturing friendships and our guild, I thought only of myself. For the longest time, I found that a terrible burden. I felt as though I had let our glorious guild down.<br>
I realized after walking the karanas alone and naked, that this was my choice, and that I had to live and or die with these consequences. No one was forcing me to stay away from my guild except me. Perhaps I was scared, perhaps I was tainted by the monotony of slaying evil and rewarding myself and my loved ones with the treasures. <br>
<br>
Choice...<br>
 <br>
Everything is choice.<br>
<br>
It was on this long journey that I finally understood, why I walk the lands of Norrath. It's not because of a personal quest that I have, it's not because riches or the mastery of skills, it is because of a single group of individuals whom wear the moniker &quot;Arrow of Light&quot;<br>
It has been a long road and a harsh battle, to even summon the courage to come back into my fold. I felt old, tired, and thought to myself &quot;So much has changed&quot;<br>
I was scared.<br>
But that fear has turned into determination, and that determination can be channeled into action. A call to arms so to speak.<br>
<br>
These are troubled times and lands we live in.<br>
<br>
We as Arrows <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>can</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>do</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">make a difference</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> in our world.<br>
<br>
I have decided that to me personally I have too much vested interest in my guild and my friends. I have decided that I am willing to &quot;by choice&quot; fight for what I believe in.<br>
So here I stand before you with blades drawn saying to you, my fellow guild mates.<br>
<br>
Please welcome back an old ranger with a few tricks still left up her ivy etched sleeve.<br>
<br>
Forever yours<br>
<br>
Merani<br>
Ranger of Karana<br>
40 seasons<br>
